																		Explanation
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/voct" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(392303); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=392303&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610182902" alt="Voct" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=392303)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/voct" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(392303); return false;" >Voct</a></span> <span class="odate time_1284817529 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">18 Sep 2010 13:45</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-876019">
									

<p>What's happening here (and I really can't think of a way for the Foundation to figure this out with the information they have) is that there's a human mind 'recorded' in the nosebag. And every time a horse sticks its nose in the bag, the mind gets imprinted on the horse (completely overwriting whatever consciousness the horse originally had - LobsterHorde suggested that the typical screaming-kicking-shitting anti-predator response manifest at this instant of the horse's mind being crushed, which is rather horrifying).</p>
<p>And then the human mind wakes up. And it's trapped in a horse body. And it fucking PANICS.</p>
<p>If the mind was able to learn, to retain memories from one horse to the next, it would eventually figure out to stop panicking, and to write in the dirt with its hooves. But every time is the first time.</p>
<p>The 'attacking its head with its hooves' thing… think of someone wiping at his eyes, trying to make himself wake up.</p>
<p>It's the mind of someone who had always, deep down, had this desire to be a horse.</p>
<p>What would it be like to have your deepest fantasy come true… and have it be more horrible than you could have ever imagined?</p>

							</div>

								
					
